NOTE ON THIRD-PARTY DATA AND ANNOTATION SOURCES

This MIT license covers the pipeline code in this repository only (the
Python stage scripts, Dockerfile, and orchestration logic). It does NOT
cover the third-party reference genomes, variant databases, and
annotation modules that this pipeline downloads and runs at build/run
time (e.g. via OpenCRAVAT). Each of those sources carries its own license
set independently by its provider.

A FULL licensing audit was performed on every OpenCRAVAT module this
pipeline could use. Commercial users must still independently verify
licensing for their specific use case — this audit reflects a
good-faith review at the time of writing, not a legal opinion.

CONFIRMED RESTRICTED — excluded from config.py's OC_ANNOTATORS:
- CADD / CADD-Exome (University of Washington) — paid commercial license
  required. https://cadd.gs.washington.edu/download
- OMIM (Johns Hopkins University) — paid commercial license required for
  any for-profit entity. https://www.omim.org/help/agreement
- SpliceAI, PrimateAI (Illumina, Inc.) — CC BY-NC 4.0, academic/
  non-commercial only. https://github.com/Illumina/PrimateAI/blob/master/LICENSE
- REVEL — freely available for non-commercial use only; contact the
  author for other uses. https://sites.google.com/site/revelgenomics/
- PolyPhen-2 — named explicitly by dbNSFP's license page as requiring
  individual commercial licensing. https://www.dbnsfp.org/license
- ClinPred — "freely available for all non-commercial applications...
  contact [authors]" for commercial use. https://sites.google.com/site/clinpred/download
- LINSIGHT — named in dbNSFP's commercial-branch exclusion list.
- MaveDB — CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 (non-commercial).
- PharmGKB — confirmed BROKEN in this OpenCRAVAT module version
  (errors on every variant), unrelated to licensing.
- CIViC, dbCID, TARGET, CScape, CScape-coding, FunSeq2, OncoKB,
  litvar_full — removed earlier for relevance/reliability reasons.

NOT CONFIRMED CLEAN — also excluded, even though no explicit
restriction was found, because no clear OPEN license statement could be
found after a genuine search either. Absence of evidence is treated as
insufficient for inclusion in a commercially-distributed default image:
BayesDel, LOFTOOL, dbscSNV, DANN-coding, ALoFT, denovo-db, ess_gene,
Pseudogene, RegulomeDB.
If you can find and confirm an open license for any of these, they can
be added back to OC_ANNOTATORS with a citation.

CONFIRMED CLEAN for commercial use — the only modules included by
default (see config.py for full citations per module):
AlphaMissense (CC BY 4.0, relicensed March 2024), gnomAD family
(unrestricted, Broad Institute), SIFT (GPL-3.0), PROVEAN (GPL-3.0),
MISTIC (MIT), RVIS (CC BY via PLOS Genetics), phyloP/SiPhy/LRT (UCSC
public conservation data), Gene Ontology (CC BY 4.0), ClinVar/
ClinVar-ACMG/GWAS Catalog (CC0), HPO (freely available, attribution
only), ClinGen (NIH consortium, built for combined academic/commercial
use), dbSNP/dbSNP-common/NCBI-Gene/PubMed/LitVar (NCBI — U.S.
government works, public domain by federal law), CGD (NHGRI/NIH,
explicit public-domain waiver), InterPro (EBI standard open-data
policy).

Additionally, this pipeline's fallback-fill stage does NOT query dbNSFP
(directly or via any intermediary) for any score, since dbNSFP's own
terms (dbnsfp.org/license) require a paid annual commercial license for
"any use within a for-profit organization" or wherever its data is
"incorporated into products or services that are sold or monetized" —
regardless of which individual score is being requested.

If you add any excluded module back in, or add any other third-party
annotation source, you are responsible for confirming its license
permits your intended use before deploying commercially.
